snippet.textDisplay: The title of this video reminds me of a time decades ago when I bought a red Fiero that was "broken."  It wouldn't start. The guy had no idea what was wrong with it.  The gas gauge said it had 1/4th of a tank of gas.  I bought it from a guy who lived in another city so I had the car towed home from there. As I was playing around with it wondering why it wouldn't start just on a whim I  poured some gas in the tank from the gas can that I had for the lawn mower. To my surprise the car started right up and ran perfectly from that moment on for the rest of the time that I owned the car.

snippet.textDisplay: The 8 rib belt is from the factory, Ford updated the pulleys after all the issues during the terminator program. If the plugs on 4 and 8 are damaged keep an eye on them, you might have an issue in the tune. Ford turns 8 down as the cooling system cannot efficiently remove the heat on that cylinder as cyl 8 is at the end of the cooling system. This issue is why there are colant crossover kits for mod motors. Just a heads up so you dont have a costly failure.
